.TH DTR 1 "May 2026" "dtr 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dtr \- a directed graph R project organizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dtr
[\fI\-h\fR|\fI\-\-help\fR] [\fI\-V\fR|\fI\-\-version\fR] \fI<command>\fR [\fI<args>\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
DTR atomizes R data analysis pipelines into nodes on a directed acyclic
graph. Each node contains a single R/tidyverse expression that chains
via the native \fB|>\fR pipe. This makes large analysis projects organized,
reproducible, and explorable.
.PP
Nodes are stored in a \fB\&.dtr\fR directory with a git-inspired backend.
Blobs (R code) are content-addressed by SHA1. Nodes use incrementing
hex IDs (n0, n1, n2, ...). CWN tracks the current working node (like
git HEAD).
.SH NODE TYPES
.TP
.B input
Read data from files or databases (dplyr).
.TP
.B process
Transform tibbles: mutate, filter, select, arrange, summarise, etc.
.TP
.B chart
Create visualizations (ggplot2).
.TP
.B model
Fit statistical models: glm, lm, etc.
.TP
.B merge
Join outputs from multiple parents (dplyr joins: inner_join, left_join, etc.).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBdtr init\fR
Initialize a DTR project in the current directory.
Creates the \fB\&.dtr/\fR backend with all required files.
.TP
\fBdtr add input\fR \fI<code>\fR [\fB\-m\fR \fI<name>\fR]
Add an input node (root, no parent). Auto-generates a marker
(\fIinput_N\fR) unless \fB\-m\fR is given.
.TP
\fBdtr add process\fR \fI<code>\fR
Add a process node (dplyr transform). Takes tibble, returns tibble.
.TP
\fBdtr add chart\fR \fI<code>\fR
Add a chart node (ggplot2). Takes tibble, returns ggplot object.
.TP
\fBdtr add model\fR \fI<code>\fR
Add a model node (glm, lm). Takes tibble, returns model object.
.TP
\fBdtr add merge\fR \fI<code>\fR \fI<parent>...\fR
Add a merge node joining 2+ parents. Parents may be node IDs or
markers. The first parent pipes via \fB|>\fR; others are assigned to
variables named after their markers.
.TP
\fBdtr add\-marker\fR \fI<name>\fR
Give the current node a human-readable nickname. Markers can be used
with \fBgoto\fR, \fBadd merge\fR, and appear as variable names in
\fBcompose\fR output.
.TP
\fBdtr add\-lib\fR \fI<package>\fR
Register an R package dependency. Packages are imported via
\fBlibrary()\fR at the top of every composed or executed script.
Duplicate additions are ignored.
.TP
\fBdtr read\fR
Print the R code of the current node to stdout.
.TP
\fBdtr write\fR \fI<code>\fR
Replace the R code of the current node. Invalidates the node's
cache and all descendant caches.
.TP
\fBdtr goto\fR \fI<target>\fR
Move to a different working node. Accepts a node ID, marker name,
\fB\&..\fR (parent), or \fB\&.\fR (child). Shortcuts error on ambiguity.
.TP
\fBdtr delete\fR [\fB\-r\fR]
Delete the current node. Without \fB\-r\fR, refuses if the node has
children. With \fB\-r\fR, recursively deletes all descendants.
Cleans up orphaned cache files. Moves CWN to the first parent.
.TP
\fBdtr compose\fR
Produce a runnable R script from the current node and all ancestors.
Package library() calls are prepended automatically.
.TP
\fBdtr run\fR [\fB\-r\fR]
Execute the current node and print the result. Without \fB\-r\fR,
skips cached ancestors (uses their stored RDS output via
\fBreadRDS()\fR). With \fB\-r\fR, forces full recomputation.
Output is also written to \fB\&.dtr/cwnout\fR.
.TP
\fBdtr cache\fR
Cache the current node's output as RDS. Runs the composed script,
hashes the result, stores it in \fB\&.dtr/cache/\fR, and updates
the node's cache field. The next \fBdtr run\fR (without \fB\-r\fR)
will use this cache.
.SH BACKEND (.dtr/)
.TP
\fBCWN\fR
Current working node (like git HEAD). Contains the node ID.
.TP
\fBcwnout\fR
Text output of the last \fBdtr run\fR.
.TP
\fBnext_id\fR
Incrementing counter for node IDs.
.TP
\fBmarkers\fR
Named references to nodes (JSON object).
.TP
\fBpackages\fR
R library dependencies (JSON array).
.TP
\fBblobs/\fR
R code, content-addressed by SHA1. Immutable.
.TP
\fBnodes/\fR
Node metadata in JSON format. Mutable in place.
.TP
\fBcache/\fR
Cached RDS outputs, content-addressed by SHA1.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Initialize a project and build a simple pipeline:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
dtr init
dtr add\-lib dplyr
dtr add\-lib ggplot2
dtr add input "read_csv('sales.csv')" \-m sales
dtr add process "filter(amount > 100)"
dtr add chart "ggplot(aes(date, amount)) + geom_line()"
dtr compose
dtr run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Navigate and edit:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
dtr goto ..
dtr read
dtr write "filter(amount > 500)"
dtr goto sales
dtr delete \-r
.fi
.RE
.PP
Cache and re-run:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
dtr run \-r          # full recomputation
dtr run              # uses cache where available
dtr cache            # explicit cache
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR R (1),
.BR Rscript (1)
.SH AUTHOR
DTR contributors.
